hands_on_practices.problem:
A continuous random variable $Y$ has a probability density function (PDF) $f(y)$ defined as follows:
$$
f(y) =
\begin{cases}
\frac{1}{4} & \text{for } -2 \le y \le -1 \\
\frac{3}{4} & \text{for } 1 \le y \le 2 \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
Calculate the expected value of the random variable $Y^2$, denoted as $E[Y^2]$. Express your answer as a single fraction in simplest form.
